==Events== *[[752 BC]] &ndash; [[Romulus]], legendary first king of [[ancient Rome|Rome]], celebrates the first [[Roman triumph]] after his victory over the [[Caenina (Town)|Caeninenses]], following [[The Rape of the Sabine Women]]. *[[509 BC]] &ndash; [[Publius Valerius Publicola]], [[Roman consul]], celebrates the first triumph of the [[Roman Republic]] after his victory over the deposed king [[Lucius Tarquinius Superbus]] at the [[Battle of Silva Arsia]]. *[[86 BC]] &ndash; [[Lucius Cornelius Sulla]], at the head of a [[Roman Republic]] army, enters [[Athens]], removing the [[tyrant]] [[Aristion]] who was supported by troops of [[Mithridates VI of Pontus]]. * [[293]] &ndash; Roman Emperors [[Diocletian]] and [[Maximian]] appoint [[Constantius Chlorus]] as [[Caesar (title)|''Caesar'']] to Maximian. * [[317]] &ndash; [[Crispus]] and [[Constantine II (emperor)|Constantine II]], sons of [[Roman Emperor]] [[Constantine I]], and Licinius Iunior, son of Emperor [[Licinius]], are made [[Caesar (title)|''Caesares'']] * [[350]] &ndash; [[Vetranio]] is asked by [[Constantina]], sister of [[Constantius II]], to proclaim himself Caesar. *[[1457]] &ndash; The ''[[Unitas Fratrum]]'' is established in the village of Kunvald, on the Bohemian-Moravian borderland. It is to date the second oldest Protestant denomination. *[[1562]] &ndash; 23 [[Huguenot]]s are massacred by [[Catholicism|Catholics]] in [[Wassy]], [[France]], marking the start of the [[French Wars of Religion]]. *[[1565]] &ndash; The city of [[Rio de Janeiro]] is founded. *[[1593]] &ndash; The [[Uppsala Synod]] is summoned to confirm the exact forms of the [[Lutheran Church|Lutheran]] [[Church of Sweden]]. *[[1628]] &ndash; Writs issued in [[February]] by [[Charles I of England]] mandate that every county in [[England]] (not just seaport towns) pay [[ship tax]] by this date. *[[1633]] &ndash; [[Samuel de Champlain]] reclaims his role as commander of [[New France]] on behalf of [[Cardinal Richelieu]]. *[[1642]] &ndash; [[Georgeana]], [[Massachusetts]] (now known as [[York, Maine]]), becomes the first incorporated city in the [[United States]]. *[[1692]] &ndash; [[Sarah Good]], [[Sarah Osborne]] and [[Tituba]] are brought before local magistrates in [[Danvers, Massachusetts|Salem Village, Massachusetts]], beginning what would become known as the [[Salem witch trials]]. *[[1700]] &ndash; [[Sweden]] introduces its own [[Swedish calendar]], in an attempt to gradually merge into the [[Gregorian calendar]], reverts to the [[Julian calendar]] on this date in [[1712]], and introduces the [[Gregorian Calendar]] on this date in [[1753]]. *[[1781]] &ndash; The [[Continental Congress]] adopts the [[Articles of Confederation]]. *[[1790]] &ndash; The first [[United States Census Bureau|United States census]] is authorized. *[[1803]] &ndash; [[Ohio]] is admitted as the 17th [[U.S. state]]. *[[1805]] &ndash; Justice [[Samuel Chase]] is acquitted at the end of his [[impeachment]] trial by the [[U.S. Senate]]. *[[1811]] &ndash; Leaders of the [[Mameluke dynasty]] are killed by [[Egypt]]ian ruler [[Muhammad Ali of Egypt|Muhammad Ali]]. *[[1815]] &ndash; [[Napoleon I of France|Napoleon]] returns to [[France]] from his banishment on [[Elba]]. *[[1836]] &ndash; A [[Convention of 1836|convention]] of delegates from 57 [[Texas]] communities convenes in [[Washington-on-the-Brazos, Texas]], to deliberate independence from [[Mexico]]. *[[1845]] &ndash; [[President of the United States|President]] [[John Tyler]] signs a bill authorizing the [[United States]] to annex the [[Republic of Texas]]. *[[1847]] &ndash; The state of [[Michigan]] formally abolishes [[capital punishment]]. *[[1852]] &ndash; [[Archibald William Montgomerie, 13th Earl of Eglinton]] is appointed [[Lord Lieutenant of Ireland]]. *[[1854]] &ndash; [[German people|German]] psychologist [[Friedrich Eduard Beneke]] disappears; two years later his remains are found in a canal near [[Charlottenburg]]. *[[1867]] &ndash; [[Nebraska]] becomes the 37th [[U.S. state]]; Lancaster, [[Nebraska]] is renamed [[Lincoln, Nebraska|Lincoln]] and becomes the state capital. *[[1870]] &ndash; [[Francisco Solano LÃ³pez (politician)|Marshal F.S. LÃ³pez]] dies during the [[Battle of Cerro CorÃ¡]] thus marking the end of the [[War of the Triple Alliance]]. *[[1872]] &ndash; [[Yellowstone National Park]] is established as the world's first [[national park]]. *[[1873]] &ndash; [[E. Remington and Sons]] in [[Ilion, New York]] begins production of the first practical [[typewriter]]. *[[1886]] &ndash; The [[Anglo-Chinese School]], [[Singapore]] is founded by [[Bishop]] [[William Fitzjames Oldham|William Oldham]]. *[[1893]] &ndash; [[Nikola Tesla]] gives the first public demonstration of [[radio]] in [[St. Louis, Missouri]]. *[[1896]] &ndash; [[Battle of Adowa]]: an [[Ethiopia]]n army defeats an outnumbered [[Italy|Italian]] force, ending the [[First ItaloâEthiopian War]]. * 1896 &ndash; [[Henri Becquerel]] discovers [[radioactivity]]. *[[1901]] &ndash; The [[Australian Army]] was formed. *[[1910]] &ndash; The worst [[Wellington, Washington avalanche|avalanche]] in United States history buries a [[Great Northern Railway (U.S.)|Great Northern Railway]] train in northeastern [[King County, Washington]], killing 96 people. *[[1912]] &ndash; [[Albert Berry (parachutist)|Albert Berry]] makes the first [[parachute]] jump from a moving [[fixed-wing aircraft|airplane]]. *[[1914]] &ndash; The [[Republic of China]] joins the [[Universal Postal Union]]. *[[1917]] &ndash; The [[Government of the United States|U.S. government]] releases the [[plaintext|unencrypted text]] of the [[Zimmermann Telegram]] to the public. *[[1919]] &ndash; [[March 1st Movement]] begins in [[Korea]]. *[[1921]] &ndash; The [[Australia national cricket team|Australian cricket team]] captained by [[Warwick Armstrong]] becomes the first team to complete a [[whitewash (sport)|whitewash]] of [[The Ashes]], something that would not be repeated for 86 years. *[[1932]] &ndash; The son of [[Charles Lindbergh]], [[Charles Augustus Lindbergh III]], is kidnapped. *[[1936]] &ndash; The [[Hoover Dam]] is completed. * 1936 &ndash; [[S.S. California strike|A strike occurs aboard the ''S.S. California'']], leading to the demise of the [[International Seamen's Union]] and the creation of the [[National Maritime Union]]. *[[1939]] &ndash; A [[Japanese Imperial Army]] ammunition dump explodes at [[Hirakata]], [[Osaka]], [[Japan]], killing 94. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Bulgaria]] signs the [[Tripartite Pact]], allying itself with the [[Axis powers]]. * 1941 &ndash; [[W47NV]] (now known as [[WSM-FM]]) begins operations in [[Nashville, Tennessee]] becoming the first [[FM radio]] station in the [[United States|U.S.]]. *[[1946]] &ndash; The [[Bank of England]] is nationalised. *[[1947]] &ndash; The [[International Monetary Fund]] begins financial operations. *[[1950]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: [[Klaus Fuchs]] is convicted of spying for the [[Soviet Union]] by disclosing top secret [[atomic bomb]] data. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Joseph Stalin]] suffers a stroke and collapses. He dies four days later. *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Nuclear testing]]: The [[Castle Bravo]], a 15-[[TNT equivalent|megaton]] [[hydrogen bomb]], is detonated on [[Bikini Atoll]] in the [[Pacific Ocean]], resulting in the worst [[radioactive contamination]] ever caused by the [[United States]]. * 1954 &ndash; [[Puerto Rican independence movement|Puerto Rican nationalists]] attack the [[United States Capitol]] building, [[United States Capitol shooting incident (1954)|injuring five Representatives]]. *[[1956]] &ndash; The [[International Air Transport Association]] finalizes a draft of the [[Radiotelephony spelling alphabet]] for the [[International Civil Aviation Organization]]. * 1956 &ndash; Formation of the [[National People's Army]] *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Samuel Stritch|Samuel Alphonsus Stritch]] is appointed [[Pro-Prefect]] of the [[Propagation of Faith]] and thus becomes the first [[United States|American]] member of the [[Roman Curia]]. *[[1961]] &ndash; [[President of the United States]] [[John F. Kennedy]] establishes the [[Peace Corps]]. * 1961 &ndash; [[Uganda]] becomes self-governing and holds its first elections. *[[1962]] &ndash; [[American Airlines Flight 1]] crashes on take off in [[New York]]. *[[1964]] &ndash; [[Villarrica (volcano)|Villarrica Volcano]] begins a [[strombolian eruption]] causing [[lahar]]s that destroy half of the town of [[CoÃ±aripe]]. *[[1966]] &ndash; [[Venera 3]] [[Soviet]] [[space probe]] crashes on [[Venus]] becoming the first [[spacecraft]] to land on another [[planet]]'s surface. * 1966 &ndash; The [[Ba'ath Party]] takes power in [[Syria]]. *[[1971]] &ndash; A bomb explodes in a men's room in the [[United States Capitol]]: the [[Weatherman (organization)|Weather Underground]] claims responsibility. * 1971 &ndash; [[President of Pakistan]] [[Yahya Khan]] indefinitely postpones the pending national assembly session, precipitating massive civil disobedience in [[East Pakistan]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; The [[Thailand|Thai]] province of [[Yasothon province|Yasothon]] is created after being split off from the [[Ubon Ratchathani province]]. *[[1973]] &ndash; [[Black September (group)|Black September]] storms the [[Saudi Arabia|Saudi]] embassy in [[Khartoum]], [[Sudan]], resulting in the [[Attack on the Saudi embassy in Khartoum|assassination of three Western hostages]]. *[[1974]] &ndash; [[Watergate scandal]]: Seven are indicted for their role in the Watergate break-in and charged with conspiracy to obstruct justice. *[[1981]] &ndash; [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] member [[Bobby Sands]] begins his [[1981 Irish hunger strike|hunger strike]] in [[Maze (HM Prison)|HM Prison Maze]]. *[[1989]] &ndash; The [[United States]] becomes a member of the [[Berne Convention for the Protection of Literary and Artistic Works]]. *[[1990]] &ndash; [[Steve Jackson Games]] is raided by the [[United States Secret Service]], prompting the later formation of the [[Electronic Frontier Foundation]]. *[[1992]] &ndash; [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] declares its independence from [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]]. *[[1995]] &ndash; [[Prime Minister of Poland]] [[Waldemar Pawlak]] resigns from parliament and is replaced by ex-[[communist]] [[JÃ³zef Oleksy]]. *[[1995]] &ndash; [[Yahoo!]] is incorporated. *[[2000]] &ndash; The [[Constitution of Finland]] is rewritten. * 2000 &ndash; [[Hans Blix]] assumes the position of Executive [[Chairman]] of [[UNMOVIC]]. *[[2002]] &ndash; [[War in Afghanistan (2001âpresent)|U.S. invasion of Afghanistan]]: [[Operation Anaconda]] begins in eastern [[Afghanistan]]. * 2002 &ndash; The [[Envisat]] [[environmental satellite]] successfully reaches an orbit {{convert|800|km|mi|sp=us}} above the [[Earth]] on its 11th launch, carrying the heaviest [[payload (air and space craft)|payload]] to date at 8500 kilograms (9.5 tons). * 2002 &ndash; The [[Spanish peseta|peseta]] is discontinued as official [[currency]] of [[Spain]] and is replaced by the [[euro]] (â¬). *[[2003]] &ndash; Management of the [[United States Customs Service]] and the [[United States Secret Service]] move to the [[United States Department of Homeland Security]]. * 2003 &ndash; The [[International Criminal Court]] holds its inaugural session in [[The Hague]]. *[[2004]] &ndash; [[Mohammed Bahr al-Uloum]] becomes [[President of Iraq]]. *[[2006]] &ndash; [[English language|English-language]] [[Wikipedia]] reaches its one millionth article, [[Jordanhill railway station]]. *[[2007]] &ndash; [[Tornado]]es [[February-March 2007 Tornado Outbreak|break out across]] the [[southern United States]], killing at least 20; eight of the deaths are at [[Enterprise High School (Alabama)|a high school]] in [[Enterprise, Alabama|Enterprise]], [[Alabama]]. * 2007 &ndash; [[Squatting|"Squatters"]] are [[evict]]ed from [[Ungdomshuset]] in [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]], provoking the [[March 2007 Denmark Riots]]. *[[2008]] &nda